===Expected Outcome===

If adopted, this proposal will provide a governance baseline for Neo that:

* affirms the need for structural governance reform;
* gives community and tokenholder legitimacy a defined role in major governance matters;
* formalizes the separation between executive and oversight functions;
* reinforces transparency and accountability as institutional obligations; and
* provides a clear foundation for resolving remaining governance design questions through dedicated follow-on work.

===Conclusion===

This proposal establishes the governance foundation that Neo should adopt as the basis for its next governance order. 
It is intended to create a durable, reviewable, and more legitimate institutional structure while enabling unresolved 
design questions to be addressed directly through subsequent governance work.

==Rationale==

This proposal establishes a governance foundation before specifying every downstream institutional detail. That 
approach is necessary because Neo first needs a common constitutional direction: governance should be structurally 
reformed, major authority should be more procedurally defined, executive and oversight functions should be clearly 
separated, and public-mission assets and decisions should be handled through stronger stewardship and accountability 
rules.

This proposal therefore focuses on first-order governance principles that should anchor all subsequent legal, 
procedural, and operational design work. More specific institutional choices may be developed in dedicated 
follow-on work, but they should be designed within this adopted governance foundation rather than in the 
absence of one.

